<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-371] lctl clear_conf documentation.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-371</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lctl clear_conf:&lt;br/&gt;
This command runs on MGS node having MGS device mounted with -o&lt;br/&gt;
nosvc. It cleans up configuration files stored in the CONFIGS/ directory&lt;br/&gt;
of any records marked SKIP. If the device name is given, then the&lt;br/&gt;
specific logs for that filesystem (e.g. testfs-MDT0000) is processed.&lt;br/&gt;
Otherwise, if a filesystem name is given then all configuration files are&lt;br/&gt;
cleared.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
